OL,3,CSister of M62 bombing victim says she
OL,4,Cremains 'devastated' by his death
OL,6,FThe sister of a soldier killed in an
OL,7,FIRA atrocity 50 years ago has said her
OL,8,Ffamily remains devastated by his death.
OL,10,FTerence Griffin was killed along with
OL,11,F11 others, including two children, in
OL,12,Fthe M62 coach bombing in Yorkshire on
OL,13,FFebruary 4, 1974.
OL,15,FGriffin was travelling with other
OL,16,Fservice personnel and family members
OL,17,Ffrom Manchester to Catterick when the
OL,18,FIRA bomb hidden in the luggage
OL,19,Fcompartment of their coach exploded.
